<p>Before opening its API to their users, they needed to secure it so that only authenticated external applications could access the API and do actions depending on their access scope.</p>
<p>I set up for that a Oauth2.0 service provider in Rails. External applications like Salesforce can now hook up Tilkee API into their own system.</p>
<p>The second part of the mission was to make the registration and login processes as easy as possible using external providers like Linkedin or Google apps.</p>
<p>If users have their google or Linkedin accounts associated, they can get authenticated in the application without having to enter any login credentials.</p>
